gue. The book highlights the inherent tensions of deliberative democracy, competing notions of representation, limitations of current conceptions of educational accountability, and the foundational importance of trust to democracy and education reform. It further provides a framework for improving community-educator collaboration and lessons for policy and practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCommunity and schoolzCalifornia. 0aDecision makingzCalifornia. 0aEducation and statezCalifornia. 0aEducational changezCalifornia. 4aEducation : Educational Administration. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791479933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791479933/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles